I don’t have insurance, my bill was $16,000. hospital has been lowering it, now at $9,500. 

They can not test me again to see if I truly recovered because even now we STILL do not have enough tests. How can we open back up if we can’t even accurately test people?

April 19th - I stopped losing weight, my headaches have mostly subsided and my stomach is getting much better. I’m still pretty tired and get a little dizzy and winded if I try and do too much, but overall feeling much better.

April 6th - I was able to come out of quarantine!

April 7th - I proposed to Jessica and she said yes!

April 9th - Back to the ER trouble breathing/GI issues, coughing lots of foamy mucus/headaches. xrays and blood tests good. told it would be another 2 weeks before better

April 3rd - still was having chest pains and labored breathing, along with severe headaches, excessive gas and other GI issues. went back to the ER. Got x-ray’d and told my pneumonia had cleared up and my blood work came back good. kept me for 8 hours to monitor me and sent home

April 3rd - still was having chest pains and labored breathing, along with severe headaches, excessive gas and other GI issues. went back to the ER. Got x-ray’d and told my pneumonia had cleared up and my blood work came back good. kept me for 8 hours to monitor me and sent home
March 27th - My breathing and O2 levels had gotten better and my fever was gone so the doctors decided to discharge me. I was told to stay quarantined and come back with any issues.

March 12th - I woke up feeling tired, feeling a cold coming on. I knew I was sick. I was on tour, we had two shows left and then the tour was cancelled. We had to drive from Denver to Chicago and then drive back to Gainesville.

Several weeks ago I was diagnosed with Covid-19, this has been my experience so far. It was pretty damn scary and I didn’t wanna talk about it for a bit. For the record this is Randy, a healthy 35 year old with no pre-existing conditions.

Having a telehealth doctors appointment right now, this is really cool. Also shout out to all of the nurses and doctors who have been helping me over the last month, I can’t even begin to tell you how much I appreciate everyone working in medicine right now. THANK YOU
